# Cloudflare Pages routing. Rules are evaluated top-to-bottom, first match wins,
# and real static assets (index.html, sandbox.html, privacy.html, /assets/*, …)
# are served before any 200 rewrite below applies.
#
# Assets first — critical: a request for a MISSING build asset must NOT fall back
# to index.html. The SPA fallback serves index.html as 200 text/html with a 4h
# Cache-Control, so a single miss during a deploy-propagation window gets cached
# at the edge — every later request for that hashed chunk then returns HTML, and
# the browser fails the module import with "Expected a JavaScript module but got
# text/html". Returning a real 404 keeps the response uncacheable-as-asset and
# lets the next request fetch the real chunk once it has propagated.
/assets/* /404.html 404
#
# SPA fallback for the client-side router (react-router). Routes like /play and
# /create have no backing file, so direct loads / refreshes resolve to index.html
# and the router takes over. Listed after the assets rule so it never shadows it.
/* /index.html 200
